DNS over HTTPS

Open the Settings app.
Go to Network & internet.
Click on Wi-Fi (or Ethernet).
Click on Hardware properties, or ignore this step if you clicked on Ethernet.
Click the Edit button next to DNS server assignment.
Select Manual.
Enable IPv4.
Enter 45.90.28.0 as Preferred DNS, then select On (manual template) and enter https://dns.nextdns.io/d8dc7c.
Enter 45.90.30.0 as Alternate DNS, then select On (manual template) and enter https://dns.nextdns.io/d8dc7c.
Click Save.

OR

NextDNS for Windows
1. Download the installer (https://nextdns.io/download/windows/stable).
2. After installing, right-click on NextDNS icon in the Systray then open the Settings. Set d8dc7c as Configuration ID.
3. Right-click on NextDNS icon in the Systray, then click on Enable.

OR

IPv6

Your network supports IPv6
1. Click on the Start menu, then click on Control Panel.
2. Click on Network and Internet, then Network and Sharing Center.
3. Click on Change Adapter Settings.
4. Right click on the Wi-Fi network you are connected to, then click Properties.
5. Select Internet Protocol Version 6.
6. Click Properties.
7. Click Use The Following DNS Server Addresses.
8. Replace the current addresses (if any) with 2a07:a8c0::d8:dc7c and 2a07:a8c1::d8:dc7c.
9. Click OK, then Close. You may need to restart your browser.

OR

IPv4 (with Linked IP)

1. Click on the Start menu, then click on Control Panel.
2. Click on Network and Internet, then Network and Sharing Center.
3. Click on Change Adapter Settings.
4. Right click on the Wi-Fi network you are connected to, then click Properties.
5. Select Internet Protocol Version 4.
6. Click Properties.
7. Click Use The Following DNS Server Addresses.
8. Replace the current addresses (if any) with 45.90.28.72 and 45.90.30.72.
9. Click OK, then Close. You may need to restart your browser.

OR

ADVANCED USERS ONLY BELOW

YogaDNS

1. Install YogaDNS from https://yogadns.com.
2. Follow the instructions for NextDNS at https://yogadns.com/docs/nextdns and use d8dc7c as Configuration ID.
